A father-of-two has been stabbed to death by a woman following a blazing row at his house. 

Kyle Farrell, 21, died from a single stab wound to the chest at the house in Dingle, Liverpool, at around 5am yesterday morning.

Mr Farrell, an amateur footballer, lived at the house with his partner Freissia and two young children. 

A 21-year-old woman, who has not been named, was arrested on suspicion of murder and remains in police custody.

