'Heartbroken isn't the word. You will be loved and missed forever.' 

Antonia Croft said: 'Rest in paradise Kyle, such a lovely lad so young as well thoughts are with the family.'

Merseyside Police's forensics teams spent a number of hours at the scene looking for evidence. 

Post mortem results will help establish the exact cause of death.

A police spokesman said: 'A 21-year-old woman from Dingle was arrested at the scene on suspicion of murder.

'She has been taken to a police station on Merseyside where she will be questioned by detectives.' 

